# Trivy CVE exemptions — narrow, per-CVE, with written reason + upgrade plan.
# Each entry MUST include the CVE id, the affected package path, the reason
# the exemption is safe today, and the trigger that retires the exemption.
#
# Adding entries here is a structural escape hatch for the Trivy gate. Use
# sparingly: prefer fixing the dep over ignoring it.
#
# ── Current exemptions ──
#
# CVE-2026-12151 — undici DoS (unbounded memory), HIGH. Fixed in undici
#   6.27.0 / 7.28.0 / 8.5.0.
#   Affected path: the node:24-alpine base image's BUNDLED npm CLI
#     (/usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm → node-gyp → undici@6.25.0). NOT an
#     app runtime dependency — the server runs `next start` (node), never the
#     npm CLI / node-gyp, so this undici is unreachable from request-handling
#     code (blast radius = build-time only). Same class as the picomatch
#     exemptions retired in the node:22→24 bump below.
#   Retire when: the node:24-alpine base image refreshes its bundled npm CLI
#     to one whose node-gyp carries undici ≥ 6.27.0 (next Node base-image
#     bump / image rebuild). Re-check with `npm ls undici` in the image.
CVE-2026-12151
#
# Historical note (cleanup-5-node-24-bump, 2026-06-14): the four
# npm-CLI-bundled CVEs that lived here (picomatch DoS / method injection
# CVE-2026-33671 + CVE-2026-33672, brace-expansion DoS CVE-2026-33750,
# ip-address XSS CVE-2026-42338) were all retired by the Node base image
# bump from node:22-alpine → node:24-alpine. The Node 24 image ships an
# npm CLI whose transitive lockfile carries the patched versions of all
# four affected packages. The exemptions are no longer needed.
#
# If a future advisory needs an exemption, include:
#   - the CVE id
#   - the affected package path
#   - WHY the exemption is safe (reachability / blast radius)
#   - the trigger that retires it (specific dep bump, base-image refresh,
#     deprecation of the vulnerable feature)
